# Walkthrough - GGUF Slot Error Handling, UI Alignment & Self-Healing

We have successfully resolved the misleading tool-calling iterations error, introduced self-healing GGUF slot recovery, fixed critical field mismatches in the Hardware tab, and aligned frontend actions with robust, backward-compatible backend API endpoints.

## Changes Made

### 1. Robust Executor Early Return

#### [agentic-chat-executor.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/agentic-chat-executor.ts)

- Replaced the loop `break` statement upon encountering an empty LLM response (`!result`) with an early return block.
- This immediately notifies the user chat that `"LLM returned no response"` instead of falling through to the end of the execution loop and displaying the misleading `"Reached maximum iteration limit"` error.

### 2. Self-Healing Model Reloading/Restarting

#### [llama-cpp-supervisor.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/llama-cpp-supervisor.ts)

- Enhanced the `loadModel` method to check if an existing matching model slot is in the `"error"` state.
- If it is, the supervisor now automatically attempts to restart the process and reload the model, allowing the system to seamlessly self-heal once underlying issues (e.g., system PATH, binary availability) are resolved.

### 3. Informative Error Bubbling with Deep Links

#### [llm-provider-manager.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/llm-provider-manager.ts)

- Instead of silently returning `null` when a GGUF model fails to bind to a dynamic port, `LlmProviderManager` now checks the slot status.
- It bubbles up the actual start-up error with an interactive dashboard deep link: `[Agentic Control / Hardware](prism://tab/agentic#tab-hardware)`.
- Clicking this deep link within the chat switches the active panel to the **Agentic Control** tab and smooth-scrolls directly to the **Hardware** slot viewer.

### 4. Front-to-Back Hardware Slot Alignment

#### [tab-hardware.js](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/public/tab-hardware.js)

- Aligned slot properties with the actual `LlamaModelSlot` snapshot shape returned by the backend:
  - Replaced all instances of `slot.slotId` with the correct `slot.id`.
  - Replaced the incorrect `slot.model` check with `slot.modelAlias` to properly detect whether a slot is occupied.
  - Expose slot-level startup error logs inline within the slot card if a slot enters the `"error"` state.

#### [dashboard-service.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/dashboard-service.ts)

- Made `/api/hardware/swarm/load` and `/api/hardware/swarm/unload` endpoints extremely robust and backward-compatible.
- They now seamlessly handle both standard `{ modelPath, modelAlias, ctxSize }` arguments and the frontend's `{ slotId, model }` parameters (automatically resolving the `modelPath` from the local `modelsDir` when needed).
