## 🚀 NEW: Dynamic Binary Paths & Readiness Auto-Healing

To address the `llama-server ENOENT` error dynamically, we have implemented a robust, user-configurable binary paths architecture and a proactive readiness auto-fix system:

### 1. Dynamic Binary Path Settings
- Added configurable text inputs for **`llama.cpp Binary Path`** and **`BitNet.cpp Binary Path`** under the **Data & Paths** section in the Settings panel.
- These settings allow you to specify the absolute path to your local `llama-server` binary (e.g., `C:\llama.cpp\llama-server.exe`) directly in the UI.
- Saving these paths immediately updates the runtime preferences and dynamically changes the supervisor's active binary configuration—**no server restarts required!**

### 2. Proactive System Readiness Checks
- Enhanced the **System Readiness** checklist in the Settings tab to run a fast validation check whenever `llamacpp` or `bitnetcpp` is the active provider.
- It tests if the configured binary path exists or is globally available in the system PATH, and checks if any active slot is currently in an `"error"` status.
- If a problem is detected, it reports a clear, descriptive warning and offers an **"Auto-Fix"** action.

### 3. One-Click Slot Reset (Auto-Fix)
- Implemented the `/api/readiness/fix/local-llm-service-ready` backend endpoint.
- Clicking the **"Fix"** button on a failed local service readiness check automatically unloads any errored slots and resets their statuses.
- Dynamic slot loading will then cleanly re-attempt starting the server and mounting your chosen model on your very next chat message!

